<P>
IRL is an object oriented infrastructure for the fault tolerance in applications working on CORBA platform.

<h2>Related Documentation</h2>
<center>
</center>
We can subdivide the IRL components in:
<ul>
  <li>DSC: the Domain Specific Components; the DSC components are: 
    <ul>
      <li><a href="irl/ogh/ObjectGroupHandler.html">ObjectGroupHandler</a>: 
      <li><a href="irl/rm/IRLReplicationManager.html">IRLReplicationManager</a>: 
        is the replication manager of the fault tolerant domain relized with IRL;
      <li><a href="irl/fm/IRLFaultNotifier.html">IRLFaultNotifier</a>: the fault 
        notifier of the domain; 
    </ul>
  <li>HSC: the Host Specific Components; the HSC components are: 
    <ul>
      <li><a href="irl/fm/LocalFailureDetector.html">LocalFailureDetector</a>; 
      <li><a href="irl/irlf/IRLFactory.html">IRLFactory</a>; 
    </ul>
  <li><a href="irl/orgw/package-summary.html">client side components (ORGW - Outgoing 
    Request GateWay)</a> 
  <li><a href="irl/irgw/package-summary.html">server side components (IRGW - Incoming 
    Request GateWay)</a>
</ul>
